article.headline: Fairfield 63, St. Peter's 60
article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) -- Mike Van Schaick scored 11 of his game-high 25 points in the final four minutes to help Fairfield rally past St. Peter's 63-60 on Sunday. Jonathan Han added 10 points, nine rebounds and five assists for the Stags (13-18, 10-8 in Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), while Herbie Allen finished with eight points, five steals and four assists. Todd Sowell led the Peacocks (5-24, 3-15) with 15 points and nine rebounds, while Kevin Spann had 10 points and six boards. The teams traded baskets for most of the day, but St. Peter's appeared to take command early in the second half, pulling out to a nine-point lead. The Stags, though, chipped away at the lead and went ahead for good when Van Schaick hit two free throws to put Fairfield ahead 53-51 with 3:06 left to play. He then stole the ball on the Peacocks ensuing possession and hit a layup to boost the lead to 55-51. St. Peter's tried to rally late and cut the lead to 62-60 on Akeem Gooding's layup with four seconds left. Brandon Brock then immediately fouled Han, who sealed the win for Fairfield by making one of two free throws.
